3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The construction of linear codes can be viewed as a problem in algorithm design, which makes this sub-category a possible fit. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Linear codes have applications in communication systems, which makes this sub-category a possible fit. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper uses twisted Kloosterman sums, which are a mathematical tool with applications in computational complexity, making this sub-category a possible fit.
